# Build artifacts / caches — match at any depth (root AND backend/).
# Plain `node_modules` only matches the root; nested copies like
# backend/node_modules leak into the build context (100+ MB) and slow
# the build / add memory pressure. Use **/ to catch every level.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.angular
**/coverage
**/out-tsc
**/tmp

.codex
.git
.history
.vscode

# Secrets — exclude at any depth (root .env AND backend/.env), but keep
# the committed example so it can be referenced.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
.npmrc

**/npm-debug.log
**/yarn-error.log

Dockerfile
docker-compose*.yml
README.md
